This paper is focused on improving the performance of the BERT model on the SQUAD2.0 dataset, which is a task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves modifications to the Transformer architecture, which is a type of neural network commonly used in NLP, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category. The paper also involves hyperparameter tuning and ensembling, which are common techniques in machine learning, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category. The paper also involves information retrieval and neural networks, so cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible categories.
